      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must have documented verification test suite and version-controlled release process consistent with MRL 2 requirements.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023R1 used under institutional SQA plan. Solver regression suite covers 47 benchmark cases including rotating machinery. Version control and change-log documentation reviewed and confirmed compliant with MRL 2 SQA expectations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via method-of-manufactured-solutions or equivalent benchmark for relevant flow physics.",
      "rationale": "Solver code verification confirmed via Taylor-Green vortex benchmark and Poiseuille flow MMS test. Hemolysis scalar transport implementation verified against analytical solution for first-order reaction in pipe flow. All convergence rates within 2% of theoretical order."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index for primary QoI (RH) must be below 5% on the mesh used for production runs.",
      "rationale": "Three-level GCI study yields GCI_fine = 1.3% for RH scalar, exceeding MRL 2 requirement. Richardson-extrapolated asymptotic solution used as reference. Spatial discretization error is the smallest identified uncertainty contributor in the total error budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) must be replicated in CFD to within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates set to within ±0.05 L/min of experimental values; rotational speed matched to ±5 RPM. Blood analogue fluid viscosity measured at test temperature and applied directly. Inlet turbulence intensity estimated from upstream pipe flow correlation and confirmed insensitive via parametric sweep."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH must agree with measured RH within combined model and experimental uncertainty at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "All five RH predictions fall within combined uncertainty bands. Model systematically over-predicts by median 4.8%, providing conservative bias. No operating point exceeds RH = 1.0 in either prediction or measurement. Comparison methodology follows ASME V&V 20 validation metric framework."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (velocity fields, RH) must be directly linked to the COU decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index is the regulatory acceptance criterion for the CPB device submission. PIV velocity fields validate the fluid dynamics driving the hemolysis scalar transport. Both QoIs are directly traceable to the COU decision on worst-case operating condition identification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid, and operating range as the COU deployment conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, identical to COU geometry. Blood analogue fluid (water-glycerol 40% by mass) used in both validation and COU simulations. Operating range 2–6 L/min at 2500–3500 RPM covers the full COU envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; iterative convergence monitoring is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, detailed numerical solver error quantification beyond iterative convergence monitoring is not required. Residuals confirmed below 1e-6 for all equations. Factor scoped to gradation 1 per MRL 2 table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; standard analyst qualification documentation is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "MRL 2 does not require formal use-error assessment beyond analyst qualification records. Lead analyst holds PhD in computational fluid dynamics with 8 years rotary pump simulation experience. Institutional simulation procedure SOP-CFD-007 followed throughout."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model must be justified for the flow regime and validated against relevant benchmark data.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on prior literature demonstrating superior performance in separated impeller flows at Re ~ 10^5. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) applied with constants from curve-fit to published erythrocyte fragility data. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±12% of RH from ensemble comparison with Bludszuweit model variant."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometric parameters, and boundary conditions must be characterized with uncertainty quantified for dominant inputs.",
      "rationale": "Fluid density and viscosity measured at 37°C; pump geometry digitized via CMM with ±0.02 mm tolerance. Inlet velocity profile derived from fully-developed pipe flow assumption validated by upstream PIV. Dominant uncertain inputs identified as impeller tip clearance and hemolysis power-law exponent via Sobol analysis conducted as part of the UQ campaign documented in the validation report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
